init_text: Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The remaining humans began to band together in small communities, and used their powers for the betterment of humanity.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Our powers are evolving in ways we never thought possible.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We had to come up with a way for us to wipe out the aliens quickly and quietly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If we could destroy their main supply of mana, we could cripple their operations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We knew the best time to attack is when they are at their weakest, in the middle of a new moon.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We had to strike now, before they were fully prepared for the new moon.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The explosion was loud and bright.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Our soldiers were armed with magic guns, which harnessed our newly found powers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The aliens became desperate and began to use their most powerful weapons.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Our soldiers were able to subdue the remaining aliens with ease.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When we finally had control of our planet, the government decided to divide it up into small communities.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Although we had finally gained our freedom, the memories of the 5 years of captivity would remain with us forever.
